title: Great Deal From Amazon and Prompt Service From Livpure
description: Everything was smooth and quick. Impressed by Livpure's promptness. Installation was done in a day. Service expert contacted even before the product was delivered. Worried about the leakage issue as mentioned in few reviews. Thankfully nothing negative happened. Water quality after 2 tank washed process improved. The flavour is exactly like packaged drinking water we buy from market. Tank doesn't take much time to fill. It is sufficient for a falmily of 4 to 5. Will review again after few days of usage.Thanks Amazon for a great deal and Livpure for a great product.

title: Really good product with little bit quality control issue
description: ¬†I'm using it for last 10 days, It's a really good product. The installation process is nice I would say. The technician told me he will come at 3pm but actually came at 5pm. After installation he left but after 15-20 min the purifier started leaking. I called the technician but he told me we will come the next day. Meanwhile I also noticed that the water opening tap is not symmetrical it's rotated slightly left. I told the technician to fix that he tried but unable to do it. So I'm stuck with it. It's working alright but wierd to look at.

After installation he left but after 15-20 min the purifier started leaking. I called the technician but he told me we will come the next day. Meanwhile I also noticed that the water opening tap is not symmetrical it's rotated slightly left. I told the technician to fix that he tried but unable to do it. So I'm stuck with it. It's working alright but wierd to look at.

title: Great Deal From Amazon and Prompt Service From Livpure
description: Everything was smooth and quick. Impressed by Livpure's promptness. Installation was done in a day. Service expert contacted even before the product was delivered. Worried about the leakage issue as mentioned in few reviews. Thankfully nothing negative happened. Water quality after 2 tank washed process improved. The flavour is exactly like packaged drinking water we buy from market. Tank doesn't take much time to fill. It is sufficient for a falmily of 4 to 5. Will review again after few days of usage.Thanks Amazon for a great deal and Livpure for a great product.

title: Not Durable and high service cost
description: The components used in this RO are not durable. These are cheap Chinese components. After 2 years you need to replace all the components be it pump, SV valve, choke etc. Also the replacement parts from Kent are double the market price with only 90 days warranty. In my view this filter is not worth buying

title: Nice Product. Installed very easily & instantly.
description: Company needs to put a visible display on front to make their customer understand when do we need to replace membrane or any part or required service or this machine has stopped working. Just one drawback.

title: Within one year internal filters got damaged as informed by Kent service guy
description: ¬†Within one year the purifier stopped working even after replacing external filter candle four time in an year. Now the kent service representative said that your internal filters and membrane are damaged .when I again enquired he said no need to change membrane and you can just change filters..kent service centre is only concerned about raising the bill amount instead of providing service that too within product warranty period...total bluff ....would recommend to prefer other filter subscription

title: Best product for us
description: ¬†We stay in rural area where we have borewell which supplies ground water, the water has different taste which is why we used to get mineral water of 20 litres from ATM machine installed in our area. It was getting tough so we wanted to try Purifier which will help purify our borewell water to mineral water. We already had Eureka but it just filtered the water, the taste did not change. We tried to save money initially as we were told the maintenance cost for Kent is high, but the other brand purifier did not help it was told RO but it dint change the taste. So we thought of giving kent a try and it was our best decision. The technician came installed explained and set tds to proper level to help us get good taste water and we are happy. It throws out waste water but we use it to wash urensils. They have free servicing for few years which is not bad. The cheaper purifiers might be less but their life is also small. I have been using this for months and it has been very helpful. If you really want change in taste of water this is good option for sure.

title: Third class...not recommended
description: I bought this product from shop. After installation it was not working properly and getting time to store the tank. So I raised query, I have to installed extra filter outside and booster pump costing for the sme was around Rs. 5-6k. Even after installing booster the performance was not good. Meanwhile, candle expired due to continues use I.e. 100 hrs or 600 ltrs which is very less as compare to other products. I had raised 7-8 tickets, even that the  product is not good and not performing well. So I decided to bought other good water filter. I am strongly not recommending this product due to its performance and heavy manitance charges which is around Rs.4-5k

title: Not Worth
description: Company claims 1 yrs warranty +3 yrs free service. This is all marketing tactics. Once 1 yr is completed when you call for free service, person will try to create mental fear factor about equipment parts & its cost and will insist to buy AMC which itself cost about Rs 7.5K - 8K. Its also not suitable where water is hard like that of underground water source. Such water will shorten life of equipment's spare parts & hence will not be pocket friendly. On every visit by service person, he will check TDS by his instrument & his readings will vary each time. So he will say that water quality is not good & hence will suggest to change parts frequently.

Once 1 yr is completed when you call for free service, person will try to create mental fear factor about equipment parts & its cost and will insist to buy AMC which itself cost about Rs 7.5K - 8K. Its also not suitable where water is hard like that of underground water source. Such water will shorten life of equipment's spare parts & hence will not be pocket friendly. On every visit by service person, he will check TDS by his instrument & his readings will vary each time. So he will say that water quality is not good & hence will suggest to change parts frequently.

title: Avoid buying this product as it requires 11000 annual maintainenace for resin replacement
description: I bought this product exactly an year back. That time the sales head of Kent told that the resign will go 5-6 years minimum. However it started giving problems in 4-5 months. Exactly after 1 year 15 days, it stopped. When I raised the request (RE-354848), the dealer told to replace the 25kg resign which would cost 11000 rupees. When I called the sales head, he told that it would go minimum 3-4 year in all parts of bangalore. There was no support from customer care apart from a standard reply that we have escalated this matter. Then they said there is no warranty on resign.  After 1 month , they closed the request giving the reason that it is unserviceable.  This is a garbage product. While selling, they would call 100 times with false promises of 5-6 years of zero maintenance and then they close the request if you don't spend 11k every year.  This product cost 80000 rupees. So if you are buyign this, think twice. You will spend 80k for one year and then 10k every year.

When I called the sales head, he told that it would go minimum 3-4 year in all parts of bangalore. There was no support from customer care apart from a standard reply that we have escalated this matter. Then they said there is no warranty on resign.  After 1 month , they closed the request giving the reason that it is unserviceable.  This is a garbage product. While selling, they would call 100 times with false promises of 5-6 years of zero maintenance and then they close the request if you don't spend 11k every year.  This product cost 80000 rupees. So if you are buyign this, think twice. You will spend 80k for one year and then 10k every year.

title: Do not buy aquaguard online
description: It is 4 months since I have installed this aquaguard and i could use this only for 2 weeks in this 4 months time. Remaining time it was down for service for various reasons. By now I have replaced all filters except RO membrane, adapter and the water control valve. The issue is still not resolved and the service is really poor. Technicians are clueless as to why the TDS value of water from RO unit is higher than the TDS of input water and why the water smell and taste is bad after so many repairs and replacements. They say since this is online purchase, they cannot do anything further. I would recommend not to buy this product online after seeing the lack of service quality especially towards online purchases.

title: Avoid this company, you will regret when any service is required
description: I purchased a machine from Livpure and could not even get it installed for months. I called them at least 5-6 separate times and they scheduled the installation, but no one would come on the day. No follow up, no message to inform. When you call again, they will act as if this never happens, and they will fix it this time. But again the same story. I finally just gave up and gave the machine to my domestic help for free when I shifted.

title: Livpure should be awarded The Most Prestigious WORST Service Award for it
description: They took 10K for AMC 2 years ago in addition to the product cost of 10K; and unimaginable proportions of recklessness & stupidity dealing with them; it has been more than 3 weeks the RO stopped working & they bloody don't care. They just a customer for life & definitely few friends in my circle. The only & best punishment I can think of, probably won't matter to Livpure but it is my small contribution.

title: Poor quality product and spares
description: Pathetic product. Purchased it last year, every month there is some issue with this RO despite good water inlet ( TDS ~ l500, clean) and voltage. Issues - Frequent waste water stopages , motor running continuosly but not filling storage tank. Had to change GKK twice. Already spent  70% of the purchase cost in very first year. My uses are decent for a small family of 4 members. Worst part is, only electrical part is covered under warranty and they don't take any responsibility of poor quality GKK kit that they are supplying at exorbitant prices. Prior to this I was using Puriet ULTIMA, it ran good for 6 years. Seems overall quality of Puriet products and spares has gone down. Thinking to switch to another brand now.
